The paper discusses the impact of cyber warfare on peace operations, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cyber conflict (cs.CY). The concept of Cyber Buffer Zones (CBZ) involves the use of technology to create a safe zone, which could fall under the category of physical security (cs.PF) and social implications of technology (cs.SI). Finally, the paper also discusses the practicalities of setting up a cyber peacekeeping component, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
